// Mob lab — basement encounter room.
//
// Layout (1600x768):
//
//   +---------------------------------------------------+
//   | ▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒ arena ceiling ▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒  |
//   |                ▒|        |                        |
//   |  hallway       ▒|        |       arena            |
//   |▒hwy ceil▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒|        |                        |
//   |                 |        |                        |
//   | [door]  [Switch]│  ░░░░░░│ [trigger]  [mobs]      |
//   |▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒▒│ ← floor
//   +---------------------------------------------------+
//                    └ jambs └─ LockWall slot ─┘
//                              (floor-level gap)
//
// Key changes from the previous draft:
// - Divider jambs only exist ABOVE the doorway opening (y=0-400) so
//   the floor-level gap (y=400-608) is always open by default. The
//   player walks freely from hallway to arena until the encounter
//   triggers.
// - LockWall fills the floor-level gap only. When the encounter goes
//   Active, the wall slams in here, sealing the player in. When the
//   encounter Clears (or the player walks back out), the wall removes
//   itself and the doorway is open again.
// - EncounterTrigger is deeper in the arena, well past the doorway,
//   so the lock wall closes BEHIND the player as the encounter starts.
//
// Static-collision authoring (Solid / OneWayPlatform / BlinkWall):
// `python -m ambition_ldtk_tools area create` automatically lowers these into the
// `Collision` IntGrid layer when this spec is applied; they don't
// appear as Ambition entity instances in the resulting LDtk file.
// Authoring rectangles by entity type stays ergonomic, but the
// canonical representation in the project is IntGrid cells (which
// the LDtk GUI can paint per cell). Live goblin_encounter in
// `crates/ambition_content/assets/worlds/sandbox.ldtk`
// already lives on IntGrid; re-running this spec preserves that.

(
    id: "goblin_encounter",
    level_id: "goblin_encounter",
    world_x: 14000,
    world_y: 1024,
    px_wid: 1600,
    px_hei: 768,
    fill_collision: "empty",
    entities: [
        (
            type: "Solid",
            px: [
                0,
                608,
            ],
            size: [
                1600,
                32,
            ],
            fields: (
                name: "floor",
            ),
        ),
        (
            type: "Solid",
            px: [
                0,
                224,
            ],
            size: [
                480,
                32,
            ],
            fields: (
                name: "hallway_ceiling",
            ),
        ),
        (
